AWKA – A man lost his life on Sunday night, while three other persons got varying degrees of injury in multi­ple auto crashes in Nnewi, Anambra State. The crash which occurred along Otolo Nnewi Road in­volved a Highlander, a Toy­ota sienna and a motorcycle. It was gathered that the driver of the Highlander on top speed lost control and rammed into the Sienna SUV and the motorcycle in front. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The Sector Commander, Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Andrew Kumapayi, while confirming the inci­dent said, “A Highlander driv­er with registration number LSD911CP lost control while on a top speed and crashed into a Toyota Sienna and a motorcycle along Otolo Nne­wi Road in front of St. James Parish at about 1540 hrs. “A total of four persons were on board consisting of four (male) adults. Three per­sons got varying degrees of in­jury and were taken to Okoro Hospital by FRSC rescue team from Nnewi Command, while the pillion on the motorcycle was taken to Akwudo Hospi­tal where he was confirmed dead by the doctor.” SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION